sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094111
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part uses BBa_J61003 as a backbone and cheY* as the inserted gene. cheY is the gene coding for cheY protein which controls flagella movement. This sequence, however, is mutated to give a mutant cheY protein which will not respond to the presence of cheZ protein. This part lacks a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Li Xinran

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Plasmid for assembly of open reading frame basic parts. A Tet promoter (r0040) and strong ribosome binding site (b0034) lie between the EcoRI and XbaI sites. Insertion of an open reading frame basic part into the XbaI and PstI sites results in constitutive expression but retains basic part utilityin standard assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094110
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the gene coding for cheY protein which controls flagella movement. This sequence, however, is mutated to give a mutant cheY protein which will not respond to the presence of cheZ protein. This part contains the coding region only.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This gene is adapted from E. Coli strain MG1655 with two point mutations (D13K Y106W)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part contains only the coding region, it is without promoter, rbs and terminator.
